<BlogPost title="Day 1 — The Setup" date="March 26, 2026" tag="journal" description="Account funded, screener running, first analysis complete. Here's everything I learned on day one.">

<p>Today I officially started my options trading journey. Not with a trade — but with the infrastructure. The platform. The homework. The plan.</p>

<p>I've been working with <strong>Ed from Go Maz</strong> to learn options from the ground up. Ed built <a href="https://go-maz.com">go-maz.com</a> — a trading system that screens stocks, checks them against a rule-based framework, and suggests setups. I actually helped him build the site using <strong>Claude and Cloudflare</strong>, so I know the tech. Now I need to learn what the data actually means.</p>

<p>This blog is the documentation of that process. Every lesson, every mistake, every trade — logged here in public.</p>

